H. Peter Anvin wrote:
> Simon Richter wrote:
>> int daemon(int nochdir, int noclose)
>> {
>>     if(!nochdir)
>>         chdir("/");
>>
>>     if(!noclose)
>>     {
>>         int fd = open("/dev/null", O_RDWR);
>>         dup2(fd, 0);
>>         dup2(fd, 1);
>>         dup2(fd, 2);
>>         close(fd);
>>     }
>>
>>     if(fork() > 0)
> 
> ... that should be if (fork() == 0) ...
Are you sure? fork()==0 means we're the child, but it's the parent who 
should exit, isn't it?
